org.eclipse.viatra.dse.solutionstore

Interface ISolutionStore

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DummySolutionStore, SimpleSolutionStore, SingleObjectiveSolutionStore, StrategyDependentSolutionStore
    Deprecated. 
    This solution store is only used by the strategies implementing the deprecated LocalSearchStrategyBase abstract class.

    @Deprecated
public interface ISolutionStore
    Interface for saving and retrieving solution trajectories. Implementation should be thread safe!

    • Method Detail

      • newSolution

        ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType newSolution(ThreadContext context)
        Deprecated. 
        Notifies the solution store of a potential solution trajectory. Note that the objectives will never be null and the implementation should be thread safe.

        Also it determines whether the execution should stop or not, if a solution is found. It can have three different responses:

        • ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType.CONTINUE: the execution should continue.
        • ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType.STOP_THREAD: this execution thread should be stopped while the others can continue.
        • ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType.STOP_ALL: the whole design space exploration process should exit.
        Parameters:
        context - Context with the actual state of the exploration process.
        Returns:
        The ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType based on it's internal reasoning.

      • getSolutions

        java.util.Collection<Solution> getSolutions()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the currently stored solutions.
        Returns:
        A collection of the currently stored Solutions.

      • registerSolutionFoundHandler

        void registerSolutionFoundHandler(ISolutionFoundHandler handler)
        Deprecated. 
        Registers a handler for executing custom code after a solution is found. When exactly it is called is determined by the implementation.
        Parameters:
        handler - The handler.

      • isStrategyDependent

        boolean isStrategyDependent()
        Deprecated. 
        If an ISolutionStore is exploration strategy dependent the framework passes the responsibility of calling the newSolution(ThreadContext) method to the LocalSearchStrategyBase implementation.
        Returns:
        True if it is strategy dependent.
